# Data model

## Team configuration

Create `data/team.json`.

Use GitHub usernames as the authoritative identity.

Example:

```json
{
  "members": [
    {
      "github": "alice-gh",
      "name": "Alice"
    },
    {
      "github": "bob-gh",
      "name": "Bob"
    },
    {
      "github": "si-gh",
      "name": "Si"
    }
  ]
}
```

Do not expose employee email addresses in the static site.

The system should use the GitHub username from `github.event.issue.user.login` when validating submissions.

The issue body may contain a display name or claimed email, but those values must never be treated as authoritative.

## Schedule configuration

Create `data/schedule.json`.

Use explicit dates rather than a computed rotation. This keeps the implementation simple and makes leave, holidays, and manual swaps easy to handle.

Example:

```json
{
  "timezone": "Africa/Johannesburg",
  "entries": [
    {
      "date": "2026-07-27",
      "github": "alice-gh"
    },
    {
      "date": "2026-07-28",
      "github": "bob-gh"
    },
    {
      "date": "2026-07-29",
      "github": "si-gh"
    }
  ]
}
```

The frontend should determine “today” using the configured timezone, not the browser’s local timezone.

The implementation should use the standard `Intl.DateTimeFormat` API or another dependency-free approach.

Provide a reusable helper for obtaining the current date as `YYYY-MM-DD` in `Africa/Johannesburg`.

## Joke suggestions

Create `data/suggestions.json`.

Use a curated local collection. Do not call an external joke API.

Support both one-line jokes and setup/punchline jokes.

Example:

```json
{
  "jokes": [
    {
      "id": "sql-bar",
      "type": "setup-punchline",
      "setup": "A SQL query walks into a bar and approaches two tables.",
      "punchline": "It asks, “Can I join you?”"
    },
    {
      "id": "udp",
      "type": "single",
      "text": "I would tell you a UDP joke, but you might not get it."
    }
  ]
}
```

Include at least 25 safe, workplace-appropriate jokes.

Prefer programming jokes, dad jokes, puns, cannibal jokes and harmless absurdity.

Do not include sexual, discriminatory, political, religious, graphic, or insulting content.

The frontend should avoid suggesting jokes already used in the archive when possible.

## Archive

Create `data/archive.json`.

Example:

```json
{
  "entries": [
    {
      "date": "2026-07-27",
      "github": "alice-gh",
      "name": "Alice",
      "type": "setup-punchline",
      "setup": "Why did the developer go broke?",
      "punchline": "Because they used up all their cache.",
      "issueNumber": 42,
      "recordedAt": "2026-07-27T07:15:00Z"
    }
  ]
}
```

For a one-line joke, store:

```json
{
  "type": "single",
  "text": "The joke text"
}
```

The archive must remain sorted by date ascending.

There may only be one archived entry per date.

