# Security requirements

The frontend is untrusted.

Never place a GitHub token in frontend code.

Never use a personal access token in GitHub Pages.

Never attempt to call the authenticated GitHub API from the browser.

Never trust identity claims from form fields.

Escape all joke content when rendering.

React’s normal escaped text rendering is sufficient; do not use `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`.

Do not execute Markdown from submitted jokes.

Treat jokes as plain text.

The GitHub workflow should use the narrowest practical permissions.

Avoid arbitrary shell interpolation of issue content.

Do not place raw issue body text directly into shell commands.

Do not allow issue content to become a filename, command, or Git argument.

