# Acceptance criteria

The work is complete when:

* The app runs locally with `npm install` and `npm run dev`
* `npm test` succeeds
* `npm run build` succeeds
* Static data validation runs as part of the build
* GitHub Pages deployment workflow is present
* A joke can be selected or entered
* Clicking submit opens a pre-filled GitHub issue
* The issue contains deterministic machine-readable joke data
* The issue Action validates the authenticated GitHub author
* A valid issue updates `archive.json`
* A duplicate or unauthorised submission is rejected
* The Action comments on and closes accepted issues
* The same workflow deploys the updated Pages site
* The schedule and archive reflect the new joke
* The archive is printable
* No personal access token or custom backend is required

